noteString: One - links to To Do Lists - Preparations
extendedNoteString:
4 Possibilities:
	Link to a Todo List that is in its keeper
	Link to a Todo Note that is in a Panel in its keeper
	Link to a Todo List that is NOT in its keeper
	Link to a Todo Note that is in a Panel that is NOT in its keeper

4 Possibilities:
	Link to a Goal that is in its keeper
	Link to a Milestone of a Goal that is in its keeper
	Link to a Goal that is NOT in its keeper
	Link to a Milestone if a Goal that is NOT in its keeper

4 Possibilities:
	Link to an Upcoming Event Group that is in its keeper
	Link to an event whose group in its keeper
	Link to an Upcoming Event Group that is NOT in its keeper
	Link to an event whose group is NOT in its keeper

noteString: Four - links to Day Notes - (today + 2 days)
extendedNoteString:
The test setup code will need to create the Group and its content.
The date to use should be today's date, plus two 
(even if that puts us into the next month/year).

The count here is the same as the non-calendar types, plus one more case for
when there is no pre-existing group to link to but for Calendar types we can
still make such a link.

noteString: Five - links to Month Notes -  (today + 2 months)
extendedNoteString:
The test setup code will need to create the Group and its content.
The month to use should be the one from today's date, plus two 
(even if that puts us into the next year).

The count here is the same as the non-calendar types, plus one more case for
when there is no pre-existing group to link to but for Calendar types we can
still make such a link.

noteString: Six - links to Year Notes -  (today + 2 years)
extendedNoteString:
The test setup code will need to create the Group and its content.
The year to use should be the one from today's date, plus two. 

The count here is the same as the non-calendar types, plus one more case for
when there is no pre-existing group to link to but for Calendar types we can
still make such a link.
